headline: New UPS air route targets trade from France to Hong Kong
summary: UPS has deployed a 747 freighter to carry French exports to Hong Kong. The primary front-haul route is typically from China and Hong Kong to Europe. The post New UPS air route targets trade from France to Hong Kong appeared first on FreightWaves.

headline: 3 US Dividend Stocks Yielding Over 3%
summary: As the S&P 500 flirts with record highs and major indexes post weekly gains, investors are closely watching the U.S. market dynamics influenced by recent economic data and policy decisions. In this environment, dividend stocks yielding over 3% can offer a stable income stream, making them an attractive option for those seeking to balance growth with reliable returns amidst market fluctuations.

headline: 3 Magnificent Stocks to Buy That Are Near 52-Week Lows
summary: D.R. Horton (NYSE: DHI), the largest U.S. homebuilder by volume, has taken investors on a roller-coaster ride over the last 12 months.  The main problem for D.R. Horton can be summed up in two words: mortgage rates.  When mortgage rates are high, fewer Americans can afford to buy new homes.
